# Manantial API

## Prerequisites

Set the following environment variables:

```bash
export MANANTIAL_API_TOKEN="your_api_key_here"
```

Generate your API key from the [/profile](<%= base_url %>/profile) page in the Manantial web application.

## Available Scripts

- **`scripts/manantial-api.sh`** — CLI tool for interacting with the Manantial API

## Setup

1. Download the script to your skill's `scripts/` directory:

```bash
curl -o scripts/manantial-api.sh "<%= base_url %>/api/skills/manantial-api.sh" && chmod +x scripts/manantial-api.sh
```

2. Set your API token:

```bash
export MANANTIAL_API_TOKEN="your_api_key_here"
```

Generate your API key from the [/profile](<%= base_url %>/profile) page.

## Usage

Run the script using relative paths from the skill directory root:

```bash
# List all posts
bash scripts/manantial-api.sh posts

# Get a specific post by slug
bash scripts/manantial-api.sh post my-post-slug

# Create a new post (title is optional)
bash scripts/manantial-api.sh create '{"title": "My New Post", "body": "Post content here"}'

# Create a post without title (note-style)
bash scripts/manantial-api.sh create '{"body": "Just some quick thoughts..."}'

# Update an existing post
bash scripts/manantial-api.sh update my-post-slug '{"title": "Updated Title", "body": "Updated content"}'

# Delete a post
bash scripts/manantial-api.sh delete my-post-slug
```

## Creating/Updating Posts

When creating or updating posts via the API, the `body` field should be provided as **Markdown**. The API will automatically convert it to HTML for storage.

```bash
# Create a post with Markdown formatting
bash scripts/manantial-api.sh create '{"title": "My Post", "body": "# Heading\n\nSome **bold** text and a [link](https://example.com)"}'
```

## API Response Format

Posts are returned with the following fields:

- `id` - Post ID
- `title` - Post title (null for notes)
- `slug` - Unique post slug for URLs
- `body` - Plain text content
- `body_html` - HTML rendered content
- `created_at` - ISO 8601 timestamp
- `updated_at` - ISO 8601 timestamp

Run `bash scripts/manantial-api.sh --help` for full usage information.
